<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2788] allow comma when specifying principals in AclCommand</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2788</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, comma doesn&apos;t seem to be allowed in AclCommand when specifying allow-principals and deny-principals. However, when using ssl authentication, by default, the client will look like the following and one can&apos;t pass that in through AclCommand.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;CN=writeuser,OU=Unknown,O=Unknown,L=Unknown,ST=Unknown,C=Unknown&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12911717">KAFKA-2788</key>
            <summary>allow comma when specifying principals in AclCommand</summary>
