                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14997702" author="junrao" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 00:04:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=parth.brahmbhatt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;parth.brahmbhatt&quot;&gt;parth.brahmbhatt&lt;/a&gt;, could you comment on this? Would it be useful to allow comma in principals when using AclCommand?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14998035" author="parth.brahmbhatt" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 06:24:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like we already have a valid use case. I will add the support for it which will mean we will either have to change the separator(My Preferred way but inconsistent with all the other CLIs) or just stop supporting more than one principal in CLI(Users will probably hate this given they will have to script it up).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14998069" author="junrao" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 06:54:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=parth.brahmbhatt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;parth.brahmbhatt&quot;&gt;parth.brahmbhatt&lt;/a&gt;, one way is to not use delimiter to specify multiple principals, and instead use &quot;--principals p1 --principals p2&quot; (see configOpt in TopicCommand).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14998899" author="benstopford" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 16:59:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll pick this one up if you haven&apos;t done it yet &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=parth.brahmbhatt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;parth.brahmbhatt&quot;&gt;parth.brahmbhatt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14998905" author="parth.brahmbhatt" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 17:04:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have started working on it, will send a PR sometime today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14998910" author="benstopford" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2015 17:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK Parth. Thanks. Ping me if you want a review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
